Class AbstractBfsIterator

java.lang.Object
  org.helm.editor.data.AbstractBfsIterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Iterator<y.base.Node>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ComponentIterator, SenseIterator
public abstract class AbstractBfsIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<y.base.Node>

Iterates over maximal connected component of nodes that satisfy isOk(Node node) condition. Also there is extension point for processing terminal nodes (non-ok nodes adjacent to this component) and boundary node (ok nodes in this component with non-ok neighbours)

Author:
Dmitry Zhelezov

isOk

protected abstract boolean isOk(y.base.Node node)
Determines whether this node is ok, that is belongs to the specific class of nodes. For example if this method always returns true, this iterator will iterate over all maximal connected components of the graph.
